SQL User Guide

sql.py - Establish connection with MySQL local database, with functions to modify and read the database structure.


InitialDB.py - Used to initial the entities and the relations between them. Only run once to build the database.

db.py - Python code used to add/delete/update the data entries with input data from the Front End.



Modify the database structure:      sql.modifyDB(db, inputQuery)
Return from the database:           sql.readDB(db, inputQuery)

QUERIES:
    Select the DATABASE to use:     sql.showDB(db, 'USE db_Name')
    Print out the Database:         sql.showDB(db, 'SHOW DATABASES')
    Print out the tables:           sql.showDB(db, 'SHOW TABLES')
    Delete the table:               sql.modifyDB(db, 'DROP TABLE table_Name')
    Print attributes from table:    sql.showDB(db, 'DESC table_Name')
    Print records from table:       sql.showDB(db, 'SELECT * FROM User')

